16/05/2004
ISLAMABAD, Pakistan -- Turkey and Pakistan are discussing joint production by their defence industries, it was announced Friday (14 May), after a meeting between Pakistani Defence Minister Rao Sikandar Iqbal and Turkish Ambassador to Islamabad H. Kemal Gur. One possible joint venture would be production of BMC military trucks. (PakistanLink, TurkeyPost - 14/05/04)
